-- MidAmerican’s Iowa Utility Unit Names Fehrman President
-- B y   J i m   P o l s o n
-- 2012-11-30T13:09:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-30/midamerican-s-iowa-utility-unit-names-fehrman-president-1-.html
MidAmerican Funding LLC, the unit of
Warren Buffett’s  Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A)  that owns an Iowa
utility, named William Fehrman president, following the
resignation of Greg Abel from that role.  Fehrman has been chief executive officer and a board member
of MidAmerican Energy Co., the Iowa utility, according to a
filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission today.  Abel remains president, chairman and CEO of MidAmerican
Energy Holdings Inc., the unit that contains Berkshire’s energy
businesses including MidAmerican Funding, spokeswoman  Ann Thelen 
said today in a telephone interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
